import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    data_grouped = data_grouped.sort_values('count', ascending=False).head(10)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data_grouped['origin'] + '-' + data_grouped['destination'], data_grouped['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Origin-Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the average number of flights between origin and destination airports
    avg_flights = data['count'].mean()

    # Create a box plot of flight counts
    plt.boxplot(data['count'])
    plt.axhline(avg_flights, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_flights:.2f}')
    
    # Set chart title and labels
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['count'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Flight Counts')
    ax.set_yticklabels([''])
    ax.set_title('Are there any outliers in the flight count data?')
    
    # Add a legend for the median value
    median_value = data['count'].median()
    ax.axvline(median_value, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from geopy.distance import great_circle

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distance between origin and destination airports
    data['distance'] = data.apply(lambda row: great_circle((row['origin_lat'], row['origin_lon']), (row['destination_lat'], row['destination_lon'])).miles, axis=1)

    # Create a scatter plot of flight counts vs distance
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['count'], alpha=0.5)

    # Set the title, labels, and legend
    plt.title('What is the correlation between flight counts and distance between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.legend(['Flights'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
